1
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:29,980
=Where Dreams Begin=

2
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:32,940
=Episode 4=

3
00:01:33,980 --> 00:01:35,180
Let me fix it for you. Give me.

4
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:54,460
You seem to be dexterous.

5
00:01:54,460 --> 00:01:55,820
I've been trained

6
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:57,140
to tear off the adhesive tape
and dress the wound.

7
00:01:57,380 --> 00:01:58,420
Every girl in the military can do it.

8
00:01:58,820 --> 00:01:59,460
Really?

9
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:02,500
Try it on.

10
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,220
Good. Very good.

11
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:15,660
Thanks, Ye Fang.

12
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,940
Why did you come to see me?

13
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:22,660
Why didn't you hang out with
Chunsheng and the others today?

14
00:02:22,660 --> 00:02:24,140
I will. I'll go later.

15
00:02:24,460 --> 00:02:25,060
To where?

16
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:26,220
Shichahai Ice Rink.

17
00:02:26,780 --> 00:02:28,540
Xiaoliu came over early in the morning
to invite me.

18
00:02:28,780 --> 00:02:29,740
He said...

19
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:33,780
You're unaware of that, right?

20
00:02:34,660 --> 00:02:35,700
Unaware of what?

21
00:02:36,220 --> 00:02:37,780
Your brother invited us to go skating.

22
00:02:38,180 --> 00:02:39,100
He and...

23
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:41,780
Are you really unaware of it?

24
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:43,700
He Hongling?

25
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:44,540
Yeah.

26
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:46,420
It seems that

27
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:47,940
he has a chance with her this time.

28
00:02:48,220 --> 00:02:49,740
So he invited us to go skating.

29
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:51,980
This is the first time.

30
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:53,380
What do you mean?

31
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:54,580
Look,

32
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,420
He Hongling used to

33
00:02:56,420 --> 00:02:57,660
hang out with Qi Tian.

34
00:02:58,300 --> 00:02:59,660
I don't know what happened.

35
00:03:00,620 --> 00:03:01,740
Your brother successfully asked her out.

36
00:03:02,300 --> 00:03:03,540
We all thought that

37
00:03:03,540 --> 00:03:05,540
she had fallen for Chunsheng

38
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:07,060
and your brother didn't have a chance.

39
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:08,780
We never thought that

40
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:10,660
he could ask her out.

41
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:12,220
Impressive.

42
00:03:13,540 --> 00:03:16,500
Do you think
He Hongling likes my brother?

43
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:17,780
You should ask your brother.

44
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:21,540
You can tell if she really likes him.

45
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:25,220
Really?

46
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:31,540
Then can you tell

47
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:32,860
if someone likes you?

48
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:33,780
Sure.

49
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:36,900
Really?

50
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:39,660
When will you go skating?

51
00:03:39,940 --> 00:03:41,300
We agreed to meet at 3 p.m.

52
00:03:41,820 --> 00:03:42,860
What about you?

53
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,220
I'll ask a friend to go with me.

54
00:03:44,540 --> 00:03:46,420
OK. Let's go together, then.

55
00:04:52,580 --> 00:04:53,460
I'm a little tired.

56
00:04:53,740 --> 00:04:54,780
You go on skating.

57
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:56,740
I'll buy you strings of candied haws.

58
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,020
Go ahead.

59
00:04:59,180 --> 00:04:59,940
I'm leaving, then.

60
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:31,100
What are you thinking about?

61
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:34,260
Nothing.

62
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:36,660
Impossible.

63
00:05:37,780 --> 00:05:38,780
You know that, too?

64
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:39,780
Of course.

65
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:41,820
Fine.

66
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:44,700
Then tell me what I was thinking.

67
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:47,500
You're jealous, but you
act like nothing has happened.

68
00:05:50,380 --> 00:05:51,140
Am I right?

69
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:54,500
Well, why would I think about you?

70
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:56,220
Look,

71
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:58,140
Guohua is from a good family

72
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:00,820
and he is good to you. Isn't that good?

73
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:02,100
I'm more than happy about it.

74
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,300
Why would I be jealous?

75
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,060
Maybe I want to provoke you.

76
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:08,260
Really?

77
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:10,740
Why do you want to provoke me?

78
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:11,780
Because you are a coward.

79
00:06:13,660 --> 00:06:14,940
Don't you agree?

80
00:06:15,460 --> 00:06:17,580
You dare not admit that you like a girl.

81
00:06:17,740 --> 00:06:19,180
Instead, you pretend
to be a loyal friend.

82
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:20,980
You double-faced man.

83
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:22,740
I'll see when you stop denying it.

84
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:28,660
Comrade He Hongling, you misunderstood.

85
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:31,700
This world is not what you think it is.

86
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,740
There's always someone
who doesn't like you.

87
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:40,180
OK.

88
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:41,540
I have to go.

89
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:01,620
Thanks.

90
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:04,780
Guohua.

91
00:07:05,020 --> 00:07:06,260
Chunsheng, here you are.

92
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:07,980
- That's exactly what I want.
- Why did it take you so long?

93
00:07:08,380 --> 00:07:09,420
The line was too long.

94
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:09,900
Try it.

95
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:10,940
This is definitely authentic.

96
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,220
It's cold.

97
00:07:12,220 --> 00:07:13,180
Let's sit down and have some wonton.

98
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:13,940
- Xiaomei.
- OK.

99
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:14,500
Where is Hongjun?

100
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:15,540
- He had to go home.
- Sir.

101
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:16,660
Wonton, please.

102
00:07:16,700 --> 00:07:17,380
OK.

103
00:07:18,180 --> 00:07:19,300
Guohua, give me a hand.

104
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:22,740
(Square Brick Factory;
State Run Snacks; Serve the People)

105
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:25,580
Guess who I just ran into?

106
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:26,740
Who?

107
00:07:26,860 --> 00:07:27,580
Zhao Yan.

108
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:29,460
Which Zhao Yan?

109
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:31,540
The secretary of
the Communist Youth League branch

110
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:32,940
in our class during our third year
of junior high school.

111
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,300
A fair-skinned girl.

112
00:07:34,780 --> 00:07:36,580
Didn't you like her?

113
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,620
Nonsense. Who told you that?

114
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:41,860
You told me yourself.
Don't you remember?

115
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:43,740
You told me while we were

116
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:45,540
learning to farm in Mentougou.

117
00:07:45,660 --> 00:07:46,300
What did you say?

118
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:47,260
OK, stop.

119
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:48,380
Don't make up stories about me.

120
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:51,380
I believe Xiao Chunsheng on this one.

121
00:07:53,540 --> 00:07:54,780
Why do you believe him?

122
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:56,180
You didn't even know him then.

123
00:07:56,180 --> 00:07:57,500
I don't have to.

124
00:07:57,580 --> 00:07:59,740
I don't believe that
he would like anybody.

125
00:08:00,740 --> 00:08:02,140
You don't know that.

126
00:08:02,460 --> 00:08:03,740
He'll meet a girl eventually.

127
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:04,700
You know what,

128
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:06,020
I really met a girl.

129
00:08:08,540 --> 00:08:10,380
The new trends of class struggle.

130
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:11,860
Why didn't you tell us?

131
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:12,940
Who is she?

132
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:14,300
You don't know her.

133
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:16,300
I don't know her?

134
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:18,860
If I don't know her,

135
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:20,260
where did you meet her?

136
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:20,980
Tell us.

137
00:08:22,580 --> 00:08:24,660
At the Neighborhood Committee
of Dongcheng District.

138
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:26,580
The entrance of the Er'tiao Alley?

139
00:08:27,940 --> 00:08:28,700
You know what,

140
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:30,300
there is a stack room

141
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:31,900
full of books confiscated

142
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:33,530
in the movements since the beginning
of the Cultural Revolution.

143
00:08:33,890 --> 00:08:35,220
Innumerable banned books

144
00:08:35,530 --> 00:08:37,500
we can't find normally.

145
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:40,010
Forget about the books.
Tell us about the girl.

146
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:42,010
Thanks, sir.

147
00:08:43,860 --> 00:08:44,780
Where were we?

148
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:46,620
Six months ago,

149
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:48,140
I found a skylight in the room

150
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:50,060
that was easy to lever open.

151
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:51,100
Since then,

152
00:08:51,420 --> 00:08:53,180
till a month ago,

153
00:08:53,180 --> 00:08:54,140
I sneaked in there

154
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,020
to read books from time to time.

155
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:58,020
I had no sooner started to go there

156
00:08:58,020 --> 00:08:59,460
than I noticed a girl

157
00:08:59,460 --> 00:09:00,220
who got in occasionally

158
00:09:00,380 --> 00:09:01,540
through the skylight too.

159
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:03,620
But I never met her.

160
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,260
Judging from the footprints

161
00:09:05,260 --> 00:09:06,500
and the books she read,

162
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:07,380
I can tell

163
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:08,820
she must be a girl.

164
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:10,660
But I had never met her.

165
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:11,660
Then I got impatient.

166
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:14,380
I sneaked into the room and hid there
several days in a row.

167
00:09:14,780 --> 00:09:16,140
Guess what?

168
00:09:16,140 --> 00:09:16,740
What?

169
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,620
I finally saw her.

170
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:20,780
Is she pretty?

171
00:09:21,460 --> 00:09:22,500
Sure.

172
00:09:24,740 --> 00:09:25,620
And then?

173
00:09:26,220 --> 00:09:28,860
Then, I dared not interrupt her.

174
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:30,020
I just sat there,

175
00:09:30,020 --> 00:09:31,140
listening to her turning pages.

176
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:34,180
She chuckled or whimpered
once in a while.

177
00:09:34,660 --> 00:09:35,460
You know what,

178
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:37,220
the girl is knowledgeable.

179
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:39,620
She probably comes from
an intellectual family.

180
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:41,700
She likes to read foreign literature

181
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:43,540
and medical books.

182
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:44,860
Most impressively,

183
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:46,540
she can read foreign books.

184
00:09:47,780 --> 00:09:48,500
Tell me about it.

185
00:09:48,740 --> 00:09:49,580
After she left,

186
00:09:50,020 --> 00:09:52,140
I would check the books she was reading.

187
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:54,460
Sometimes she couldn't find a book
she wanted to read.

188
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:55,700
But I know where it was.

189
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:56,820
So I dug it out...

190
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:57,340
Eat.

191
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:58,740
And put it on the bookshelf
closest to her.

192
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,140
Just like that,

193
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:04,500
we spent some time together.

194
00:10:05,820 --> 00:10:07,060
About a month ago,

195
00:10:07,620 --> 00:10:09,060
on the day you met Hongling,

196
00:10:09,380 --> 00:10:11,540
I made up my mind to say hello to her.

197
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:12,940
And then?

198
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:14,060
Then?

199
00:10:14,460 --> 00:10:15,980
Then I walked towards her

200
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:17,300
from where I was,

201
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:18,780
intentionally making some noise.

202
00:10:19,020 --> 00:10:20,620
She was scared and tried to avoid me.

203
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:23,940
I was about to catch up with her,

204
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:25,100
not expecting that...

205
00:10:25,860 --> 00:10:26,500
What?

206
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:28,460
The door suddenly opened.

207
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:31,860
It turned out that the guard always
heard noises in the room.

208
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:32,900
He thought it was haunted.

209
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:33,860
So he brought the security over,

210
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:35,620
stripped the seal, and went in to check.

211
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:36,740
They had no sooner got in

212
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:38,500
than they heard the girl's footsteps.

213
00:10:38,500 --> 00:10:39,940
They ran directly towards her.

214
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:41,140
Whoops!

215
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:42,140
Then what?

216
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:44,380
I thought the girl was in trouble.

217
00:10:44,660 --> 00:10:45,780
Fortunately, I had a flash of wit.

218
00:10:45,860 --> 00:10:46,940
I pushed the bookshelf over.

219
00:10:46,940 --> 00:10:47,940
Bang,

220
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:50,220
they thought they ran
in the wrong direction.

221
00:10:50,220 --> 00:10:51,540
So they turned around
and came after me.

222
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:53,580
They never thought that

223
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:56,420
there were two enemies reading
the poisonous books.

224
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:58,140
Make a feint to the east
but attack in the west.

225
00:10:58,260 --> 00:10:59,260
You get it right.

226
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:00,620
Then what happened?

227
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:02,060
Did the girl escape?

228
00:11:02,180 --> 00:11:02,740
Of course.

229
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:04,660
What about you?

230
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:06,820
I?

231
00:11:07,540 --> 00:11:08,780
I was caught by them.

232
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:11,940
Then what happened to you?

233
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:13,740
How could

234
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:15,020
such a petty thing stump me?

235
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:16,740
Don't worry. I escaped unscathed.

236
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:17,820
Nothing happened.

237
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:19,980
But it's a shame that

238
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:21,780
I can't go there to read anymore.

239
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:25,060
Where was the girl?

240
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:26,940
She had long gone.

241
00:11:28,220 --> 00:11:29,140
Have you never seen her again?

242
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,380
You've never talked to her,

243
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,660
but you take a fancy to her?

244
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:35,580
You know what,

245
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:36,820
I don't have to talk to her.

246
00:11:37,140 --> 00:11:38,460
Seeing the books she read,

247
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:39,980
I know exactly what was on her mind.

248
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:42,420
So, find her.

249
00:11:42,580 --> 00:11:43,420
How could I?

250
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:46,260
She must be looking for you, too.

251
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:49,700
She must know that you saved her.

252
00:11:52,060 --> 00:11:53,900
Do you know what she looks like?

253
00:11:55,180 --> 00:11:56,220
Of course.

254
00:11:56,740 --> 00:11:57,620
A piece of cake.

255
00:11:57,780 --> 00:11:59,460
Draw a picture.
Just like you drew the picture of me.

256
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:01,500
Right, Chunsheng.

257
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:02,620
Draw her portrait.

258
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:04,460
Yeah, draw her portrait.

259
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:05,740
Hang it over the rink.

260
00:12:05,940 --> 00:12:07,060
Let everyone help you to look for her.

261
00:12:07,140 --> 00:12:08,300
Maybe I know her.

262
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:10,020
If you can't draw her portrait,

263
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:11,500
there must be a problem.

264
00:12:15,220 --> 00:12:16,500
What problem?

265
00:12:17,740 --> 00:12:18,900
That means there wasn't such a girl.

266
00:12:19,380 --> 00:12:20,500
He made up a story.

267
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:26,900
Sir, a portion of fried sausage.

268
00:12:28,460 --> 00:12:29,060
Chunsheng,

269
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:30,740
was there really

270
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:33,380
such a girl?

271
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:34,940
Are you doubting me?

272
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:36,500
Have I ever lied to you?

273
00:12:37,940 --> 00:12:38,700
Have some wonton.

274
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:44,020
Who wants chestnuts roasted with sugar?

275
00:12:44,260 --> 00:12:44,900
Follow me.

276
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:45,700
Me.

277
00:12:46,380 --> 00:12:46,900
Go.

278
00:12:47,420 --> 00:12:48,020
Wait for me.

279
00:12:58,620 --> 00:12:59,220
Xiaomei,

280
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:00,700
would you like fried sausage?

281
00:13:02,260 --> 00:13:03,140
I'll get some for myself.

282
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:18,220
What's on your mind?

283
00:13:21,380 --> 00:13:21,900
Fang,

284
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:24,820
what's wrong with you guys today?

285
00:13:25,020 --> 00:13:26,300
Why are you so concerned about me?

286
00:13:26,460 --> 00:13:27,700
I want to warn you.

287
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:30,260
OK.

288
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:31,540
Go ahead.

289
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:33,100
Don't do my brother harm.

290
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:36,900
What did I do?

291
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:38,860
You're going to
give up He Hongling to him.

292
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:40,980
How do you know?

293
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:42,580
Is it in the newspaper

294
00:13:42,580 --> 00:13:43,940
or announced in the military?

295
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:45,460
Don't talk glibly to me.

296
00:13:45,860 --> 00:13:47,500
I was there and I saw everything.

297
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:49,140
Everyone with discerning eyes can tell.

298
00:13:49,660 --> 00:13:51,500
Do you think we can't tell?

299
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:53,660
Nobody is stupid
unless they pretend to be.

300
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:56,380
I don't know if others are stupid.

301
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:59,100
But you are too smart.

302
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,220
If it weren't for my brother,

303
00:14:00,580 --> 00:14:02,500
I wouldn't spare time
to meddle in your affairs.

304
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:04,220
Fang, let me tell you.

305
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:05,740
He's also my buddy,

306
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:07,500
the one who's closer to me
than my own brother.

307
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:08,460
As far as I know,

308
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:10,500
Guohua likes He Hongling

309
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,220
and she didn't turn him down.

310
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:13,740
I just think that

311
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:14,580
she's the kind of girl

312
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,580
who knows exactly what she wants.

313
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:18,180
